summary: by Troglodyte The Neanderthal/Music Video/iTunes/Spotify) URBAN VAULT UK HIP HOP/RAP/R&B/UNDERGROUND MUSIC NEWS/INTERVIEWS/EVENTS Main menu Skip to content UK Music News U. Louis, Missouri-based emcee Daemon recently released the visual to his track THREE YEARS SOBER, produced by fellow St. Louis-based Troglodyte The Neanderthal Daemon presents the Digital Co-Op-directed video for ‘Three Years Sober’, which continues a string of releases from Daemon as of late, including ‘Comfortable‘, ‘ROTN – Inertia‘, ‘Credit Check‘, ‘Elevation‘, and ‘Vader‘. Daemon marries a golden-era Hip Hop pedigree with a trailblazing spirit, routinely weaving genres as disparate as EDM, Trap, and Grunge into the mix. Daemon has collaborated with artists like Killer Mike, DJ Shadow, and Trackstar The DJ of Run The Jewels.
